headline.main: From Boston.; ARREST OF ALLEGED SLAVE-TRADERS--THE INDIAZ RUBBER CAR-SPRING CASE--DEATH OF REV. DR. PEABODY--MR. BURLINGASIE.

docs.lead_paragraph: Messrs. JOAQUIN, NEGRET, and DE MENA, the latter a well-known cigar doaler of this city, have been arrested and hold to bail in the sum of five and ten thousand dollars respectively, on charges of having been engaged in the Slave-trade. They will be examined before Commissioner WOODBURY, on Monday next.
